The paper deals with finite automata running over infinite binary trees, which is a topic in formal language theory (cs.FL). The paper also introduces a game to prove the regularity of languages accepted by automata with cardinality constraints, which is related to logic (cs.LO). The concept of accepting and rejecting branches in the automata also involves the study of sets and their properties, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the topological properties of the set of accepting branches, which is related to graph theory (cs.GT) and computability theory (cs.CC).
